SIMPLE: earthy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Earthy
<hw>Earth"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Consisting
of, or resembling, earth; terrene; earthlike; <as>as, <ex>earthy</ex>
matter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How pale she looks,⟦br⟧
And of an <qex>earthy</qex> cold!</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All over <qex>earthy</qex>, like a piece of earth.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the earth or to, this world;
earthly; terrestrial; carnal.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Their
<xex>earthy</xex> charge.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The first man is of the earth, <qex>earthy</qex>; the second man
is from heaven. As is the earthy, such are they also that are
<qex>earthy</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>1 Cor. xv. 47, 48 (Rev. Ver.
)</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Earthy</qex> spirits black and envious are.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Gross; low; unrefined.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Her
<xex>earthy</xex> and abhorred commands.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Without luster, or dull and
roughish to the touch; <as>as, an <ex>earthy</ex>
fracture</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Earwax</ent>⟦br⟧
